Elements.Title: Panel Lines (upper)
Elements.Description: [CTRL]+[F4]

Elements.Title: Targeting Reticle
Elements.Description: Cycle through reticle colours with [F7]

Elements.Title: Environment Target Colour
Elements.Description:
Indicates current and possible destination targets, such as planets, stations.
Cycle through Environment target Colours with [CTRL]+[F7]

Elements.Title: Hud Dimmer
Elements.Description:
Cycle with [F5].
There are 6 levels of brightness (5,4,3,2,1,0).

Elements.Title: HUD and Panel Opacity Layer
Elements.Description: The colour of the background behind the panels

Elements.Title: Text Colour
Elements.Description: If Text Colour is set to 4 then you can choose your own text colour.

Elements.Title: Text Custom Color
Elements.Description: Please note, the XML shader will overlay the text and modify the text colour. There is no way to prevent this from happening.

Elements.Title: Text Brightness
Elements.Description: Brightness for Texts

Elements.Title: Panel Lines (lower)
Elements.Description: [ALT]+[F4]

Elements.Title: Panel Opacity Boost
Elements.Description: Transparency of the Shadows behind Panels and HUD elements.

Elements.Title: Ambient Cabin Lights
Elements.Description: Cycle with [CTRL]+[F6].

Elements.Title: Cabin Lighting Style
Elements.Description: Restricted (Elite standard, cabin light doesn't cover whole cockpit)

Elements.Title: Night Vision
Elements.Description: Night Vision

Elements.Title: Lighting Dimmer
Elements.Description: Cycle with [F6]. Each press of F6 reduces the cabin lighting brightness by 0.2 (20%)

Elements.Title: OwnCarrier Highlight
Elements.Description:
OwnCarrier Highlight on Nav panel (also highlights the current planetary bearing indicator on the landing reticle/SRV).
(OFF will show the XML matrix colour)

Elements.Title: OwnCarrier Highlight Color
Elements.Description: Note: A custom XML will modify this colour. Base colour refers to the colour on orange Elite panels.

Elements.Title: Orbit Lines
Elements.Description: Orbit Lines (and Exclusion Zone Lines) & Gravity Well Lines ** (Supercruise only)

Elements.Title: Orbit Lines Brightness
Elements.Description: Orbit Lines Brightness. Try 0.05 or 0.1 for very dim lines. Turn off with 0.0

Elements.Title: Gravity Well Lines
Elements.Description: Gravity Well Lines colour

Elements.Title: Gravity Well Brightness
Elements.Description: Gravity Well Lines Brightness

Elements.Title: Planetary Landing Reticle
Elements.Description: Planetary Landing Reticle ** Bearing and descent angle bars

Elements.Title: Supercruise Speed Lines
Elements.Description: supercruise speed lines colour

Elements.Title: Supercruise Speed Lines Brightness
Elements.Description: Supercruise Speed Lines Brightness ** (range 0 to 1) (0 = OFF)

Elements.Title: Supercruise Dust
Elements.Description: Supercruise Snow / Convergent white lines

Elements.Title: Space Dust
Elements.Description: Space Dust (in normal flight)

Elements.Title: DSS Overlay
Elements.Description: Setting to OFF will remove the green / blue overlay while the DSS is not active

Elements.Title: Dirty streaks on canopy windows
Elements.Description: You can turn off the dirty streaks on the canopy windows if you prefer a 'cleaner' look :)

Elements.Title: Use XML
Elements.Description:
Toggle XML for CHUD & A-HUD ** [CTRL ALT X]
For technical reasons we cannot mix EDHM CHUD/A-HUD colours with XML CHUD/A-HUD colours (it causes glitches with some combinations)

Elements.Title: Brightness
Elements.Description: AHUD & CHUD Brightness

Elements.Title: CHud Color
Elements.Description: Cycle through CHUD colours with [CTRL]+[F2]

Elements.Title: CHud Mode
Elements.Description: [SHIFT]+[F2] to swap between modes

Elements.Title: AHud Inner Lines
Elements.Description: Cycle through A-HUD colours with [ALT]+[F2].

Elements.Title: AHud Outer Lines
Elements.Description: Cycling through colours will change both the inner lines and the outer lines together.

Elements.Title: HUD Common Group
Elements.Description: [CTRL]+[F5]. The Common Group comprises the fuel bar, indicator lights, hologram swirls, ship status bar, hull bar, and outer radar elements

Elements.Title: Radar Colour
Elements.Description: Cycle through radar colours with [F4]

Elements.Title: Radar White-coloured Objects
Elements.Description: Turn off white-coloured objects on the radar (materials, wakes, etc). Toggle with [CTRL]+[ALT]+[W]

Elements.Title: Shield Color
Elements.Description: Cycle with [F2]

Elements.Title: Hologram Mode
Elements.Description: Ship only, not SRV [CTRL]+[F3]

Elements.Title: Holo Color
Elements.Description: Cycle through OwnShip hologram colours with [F3]

Elements.Title: Hologram Dimmer
Elements.Description: Each press of [ALT]+[F3] dims the hologram by 10% (1.0, 0.9, 0.8, 0.7, etc)

Elements.Title: Hologram Shimmer
Elements.Description: shimmering lines on the Holo

Elements.Title: Target Hologram Custom Color
Elements.Description: Custom Color for Target Hologram - Neutral Colour.

Elements.Title: Target Hologram Brightness
Elements.Description: Brightness for Target Hologram - Neutral Colour.

Elements.Title: Target Hologram Shimmer
Elements.Description: shimmering lines on the Holo

Elements.Title: Power Distributor
Elements.Description: [ALT]+[F5]

Elements.Title: Signature Bar Colour
Elements.Description: Cycle through Signature Bar colours (looks like a radio signal) colours with [SHIFT]+[F4]

Presets.Name: Light blue / Dark Blue / Orange / Red
